<br>
My eyes widen as they make out the shape of a troll running straight for me, a large, gnarled club held in huge, clawed hands. Then I notice a smaller form just ahead of him. It takes me an instant to recognize my Nana---Marha---running from the troll, her skirts hiked above her knees, her normally pleasant dwarven face distorted into a mask of fear as her screams break the silence of Felwithe. <br>
<br>
&quot;Marha!&quot; I gasp, summoning the power to smite the troll. At the back of my mind, I sense something not right with the scene before me, but with little time to think it over, I smite the troll with my strongest spell. The troll staggers and I see Marha's eyes light up with hope---but just then I see what is <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>wrong</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> with the scene unfolding before me. Firstly, Marha's feet are moving frantically, but the speed at which she approaches me is unrealistically slow. It is as if she is suspended in time, each desperate stride only taking her no farther than a baby-step from her attacker. <br>
<br>
Secondly, there is a peddler pushing his cart down the street, and he looks up, removes his hat, and bows to me cordially, but <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>does not even glance at the troll.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> These thoughts come to me so quickly, that before I sort them out, I scream as the club comes crashing down on Marha's head in a spray of blood and brains. <br>
<br>
And then Marha and the troll just blink out, as if they were never there. There should have been blood on the cobblestones. Even the echo of her screams resounding off of the manors. But all was silent. <br>
<br>
The peddler stands gaping at me, then hurriedly grasps the handles of his cart and runs off, with one final look over his shoulder at the madwoman he thinks me to be. And indeed, mad I must be, because I hear footsteps running to the door and Marha calling out to my father to come quickly, that she was napping and heard a scream outside the door. Panicking, I weave the simple magicks of a gate. I can't let them see me, for the first time in years, in this state.<br>
<br>
Something very bizarre is happening to me, and I need to figure out its nature before allowing myself close to those I love so dearly. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=isharramoonsong>Isharra Moonsong</A> at: 12/8/02 10:39:18 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=isharramoonsong>Isharra Moonsong</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 675<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/8/02 10:39:00 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=326.topic&index=62>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.earthlink.net/~brennec/_uimages/Isharra.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Flight from Felwithe</span><hr size=1> (wow, lots of stuff happening right now... hard to keep updated)<br>
<br>
~~Some time after Isharra's trouble in Felwithe~~<br>
<br>
The ointment Isharra applied to the wound on her arm eased the pain a bit, but did nothing to heal it. The Shamaness had seemed doubtful that it would work, especially since Isharra's own powerful magicks had done nothing to cure the twin puncture wounds on her arm. <br>
<br>
And even more troubling was her constant state of thirst---no, more like hunger. But she would <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>not</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> allow herself to feed on that which would ease her deteriorating condition. She had not chosen this path for herself, but she would make choices now that would determine her fate, if she could. And her first choice was to find a cure for this god-forsaken disease, if it could indeed be called that. <br>
<br>
&quot;You must kill the one who turned you. . .&quot; the voice of a memory whispered in her mind. But how was that possible when the one who turned you was so powerful? <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=isharramoonsong>Isharra Moonsong</A> at: 12/9/02 2:41:41 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=smallcutepuppy>smallcutepuppy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 646<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/9/02 12:40:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=326.topic&index=63>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Flight from Felwithe</span><hr size=1> (( Can't wait to see where this goes. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  )) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=isharramoonsong>Isharra Moonsong</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 681<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/9/02 12:45:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=326.topic&index=64>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.earthlink.net/~brennec/_uimages/Isharra.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Flight from Felwithe</span><hr size=1> (( I can't either... I'm just playing it by ear. I didn't 